<h2> How to Make a DIY Flower Vase </h2>

<h3> 1. Tie the yarn twice around the glass bottle. </h3>
 
<h3> 2. Cut off the excess and remove the yarn from the bottle. </h3>

<h3> 3. Fill a small bowl with pure acetone, then submerge the yarn in the acetone </h3>

<h3> 4. Remove the yarn from the acetone and place it back around the bottle. </h3>

<h3> 5. Use a lighter to ignite the yarn. </h3>

<h3> 6. Spin the bottle continuously to ensure all of the yarn ignites. </h3>

<h3> 7. Dunk the glass into a pitcher of cold water. </h3>

<h3> 8. Remove the bottle. The top of the glass should fully detach from the base of the bottle. </h3>

<h3> 9. Sand down the rough edges of the glass until smooth. </h3>

<h3> 10. Apply a strip of tape around the bottle, about half an inch from the rim. </h3>

<h3> 11. Paint the rim of the bottle with an acrylic paint of your choice. Remove the tape after the paint has dried. </h3>

<h2> 12. Enjoy your new one-of-a-kind vase! </h2>

